sql:
SELECT course_name
FROM courses
WHERE credits = (SELECT MIN(credits) FROM courses);

external_knowledge:
- "blossoming flowers" metaphorically refers to the courses;
- "average sunlight" represents the average grade received in the course;
- "at least one petal" symbolizes the condition where a course has at least one assignment.

sql:
SELECT type_name
FROM assignment_types
WHERE LENGTH(description) > 10;

external_knowledge:
Decently scored: achieving at least half the maximum points for the assignment;
Late submission: marked as '1' or 'true' in the 'late_submission' field;
Enrolled status: indicates active participants in the courses; 
Standing: total grades, number of submissions, and average grade per student.
